Bolsa Família was a social welfare program of the Government of Brazil, part of the Fome Zero network of federal assistance programs. Bolsa Família provided financial aid to poor Brazilian families; and if they had children, families must ensure that the children attend school and are vaccinated. If they exceed the total of permitted school absences, they are dropped from the program and their funds are suspended. The program attempts to both reduce short-term poverty by direct cash transfers and fight long-term poverty by increasing human capital among the poor through conditional cash transfers. It also works to give free education to children who cannot afford to go to school to show the importance of education In 2008, The Economist described Bolsa Família as an "anti-poverty scheme invented in Latin America which is winning converts worldwide. This dataset collects information from 110k medical appointments in Brazil and is focused on the question of whether or not patients show up for their appointment. A number of characteristics about the patient are included in each row.

Data Definition:

  • PatientId: it's unique identification number for each patient.
  • AppointmentID: it's an identification number for each appointment.
  • Gender: Male or Female.
  • AppointmentDay: date of actual appointment.
  • ScheduledDay: the day patient reserve for appointment.
  • Age: age of patient.
  • Neighborhood: the place that patient takes the servise.
  • Scholarship: 1 or 0.(goverenmental support to poor people to learn their kids)
  • Hipertension: 1 or 0.(chronical disease for high blood pressure)
  • Diabetes: 1 or 0. (chronical disease for high sugar percentage in blood)
  • Alcoholism: 1 or 0.(used to drink alcohol ... alcohol addict)
  • Handcap: 1 or 0.(have a physical body movement problem)
  • SMS_received: messeages sent to patient to insure the appointment date.
  • No_show: "Yes" or "No". (the status of attending the appointment on schedualed date or not).

# functions used to draw all histogram plots 
def hist_fun(df, title, x, med , bins , log) :
    df.hist(bins = bins, edgecolor='black', log=log, xlabelsize =12, xrot =45, yrot = 45, grid=True, figsize =(12,6));
    plt.title(title , fontsize =16);
    plt.xlabel(x , fontsize ='large');
    plt.ylabel('no of samples' , fontsize = 'large')
    plt.axvline(med, color='r',label= 'med '+ x , linewidth=2)
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
In [44]:
# drawing bar chart
def bar_fun(df,x, title , rot =0):
    colors = ['red', 'blue']
    df.plot(kind='bar', title=title ,color=colors, alpha=.7 , figsize =(16,8) , rot =rot );
    plt.xlabel( x , fontsize=18 )
    plt.ylabel('count', fontsize=18)
    plt.legend()
In [45]:
def bar_fun_2(df , title ):
    colors = ['red', 'blue']
    df.unstack('no_show').plot(kind="bar", color = colors ,stacked=False,figsize=(12,6),grid=True , rot = 0) #plot for the grouped dataframe
    plt.title(title) #change title for the plot
    plt.legend(["Show up", "Didn't showed up"]); #change legend for each color of data
    plt.ylabel("count of patients")

limitations¶

1-there are 48228 patients have repeated visit according to there repeated patientid no so the real count of cell that we are working with is 62299

2-the actual location of neighnourhood is not mentioned so we can't judge exactly what is the effect of neighbourhood on data analysis

3- handicap column contains values other than 0 , 1 whish is not clear what is that exactly means so i change all the values other than one to one

4- as there error in age recording also errors on schedueld date after appointment date this makes some doubt about data recording

5- it's not mentioned if this dataset is enough to evaluate a huge governemental project as bolsa familia because it's not clear how mush time this dataset data collected time

Summary And Conclusion¶

1- nighbourhood supposed to add more informations to has significant effect od data analysis

2- patient id and appointment id has no significant effect on data specially there are 48228 record repeated for the same patients

3- gender has no significant effect on data as the number of male almost the same as the number of female

4- schoolar ship has significant effect on data anlysis

5- chronical disease have significant effect on data anlysis

6- waiting days has significant effect on data analysis

7- age has significat effect on data analysis

8- saturday is the most highest value of patients didn't show up
